 medical practice on physicians and medicine since World War II. Based on the authors' original scholarship, these essays offer an excellent and very accessible introduction to an important and controversial subject. They are also particularly relevant in light of current controversies over the nature and application of research in human genetics and biotechnology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aMedical ethicszGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aMedicinezGermanyxHistoryy20th century. 0aNational socialismxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xAtrocities. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Germany.2bisacsh1 aAllen, Garland E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurleigh, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedlander, Henry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuener, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuener, Jonathan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKater, Michael H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNicosia, Francis R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNicosia, Francis R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aProctor, Robert N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSeidelman, William E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745692240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857456922423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857456922/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13E